From 2c5c2bafb8c078ab38eb223fd7ddf0b296ab443b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 12:23:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0894: per-subtype priority + earnings-with-dividend
 label composition

MARKSANS bug after 0891: had EARNINGS and DIVIDEND_DECLARATION in same
days news set. Per-CatalystType priority ranked MNA (100) above
EARNINGS (60), so the routine dividend won over the actual Q4 results
and the row showed "dividend declared" alone.

User audit: dividend / bonus / stock-split declarations are typically
ACCOMPANIMENTS to earnings (companies declare them WITH their quarterly
print). They should not outrank the earnings itself.

Fixes:

1. Replaced per-CatalystType priority with per-NewsSubType priority.
   Now routine accompaniments are explicitly low:
     DIVIDEND_DECLARATION  30
     INTERIM_DIVIDEND      30
     BONUS_ISSUE           35
     STOCK_SPLIT           35
   - below EARNINGS_RESULTS (70). Actionable M&A stays high:
     ACQUISITION, OPEN_OFFER, MERGER_SCHEME       100
     PREFERENTIAL_ALLOTMENT, BUYBACK              85-90
     GUIDANCE_RAISE / GUIDANCE_CUT                90
     USFDA_APPROVAL / USFDA_OBSERVATION           85
   Full table covers ~50 subtypes with deliberate priority bands.

2. Label composition: after picking the top catalyst, scan remaining
   articles for routine accompaniments. If top is EARNINGS_RESULTS
   and another article carries DIVIDEND/BONUS/SPLIT, append
   "+ <accompaniment>" to the label. So MARKSANS now reads:
     "earnings result + dividend declared"
   instead of either alone. Same for ORDER_WIN + dividend, etc.

For other movers:
  - BLISSGVS (already correct): "Anupam Rasayan -> 43% stake...
    CONTROL SHIFT..." stays unchanged - ACQUISITION still wins.
  - ASTRAMICRO (had "dividend declared"): if it also has earnings
    news, will now show "earnings result + dividend declared".
